[Approach - 1] Using Simple Traversal - O(n) Time and O(1) Space
The idea is to traverse the array once and count how many times the same value repeats consecutively. 
The thought process is to use a counter that increases when the current element matches the previous one. 
If a change is detected, we update the maximum streak and reset the count. 
-----------------------------------------------------


[Approach - 2] Using Bit Manipulation - O(n) Time and O(1) Space
The idea is to use XOR (^) to check if consecutive elements are the same. 
As XOR of two numbers is 0 if both numbers are same. So, If prev ^ num == 0, the sequence continues; 
else we update the maximum streak and reset the count.
----------------------------------------------------------

static int maxConsecBits(int[] arr) {
    if (arr.length == 0) return 0; 

    int maxCount = 0, count = 0, prev = -1;

    for (int num : arr) {
        
        // If the current number is the 
        // same as the previous number
        if ((prev ^ num) == 0) {
            count++;
        } else {
            
            // Update maxCount and reset count
            maxCount = Math.max(maxCount, count);
            count = 1;
        }
        prev = num;
    }

    return Math.max(maxCount, count);
}
